# Re-voice the Bugle: Briefing Prose From the Extraction Prompts

## Step

The paper writes ABOUT Joel in LLM-newspaper register — today's lead: "Joel's Private Wiki Moves From Architecture Notes to the Front Page Test", loops that need "his brain next". Charter says briefing voice: the paper talks to *you*.

Rewrite the pi extraction + edition prompts (`open-loop-extractor.ts`, edition lead/theme prompts) so every prose field — headline, framing, whyItMatters, question, theme, change digests — lands in briefing voice: second person, sentence-case headlines as direct statements (loopcraft's "Build a local issue-progress loop you can trust." is the register), short sentences, contractions, ELI5-but-technical (unpack jargon in place, one clause, no dumbing down), `joel-writing-style` anti-patterns banned (no "leverage", no "key insight", no Title Case theater), Fabrication Rule enforced — no invented specifics; a claim either cites observations or doesn't get written.

Deliverable is a prototype Joel reads: bump the prompt contract version (promptHash), rebuild a real edition, show before/after side by side, pin regression examples (good/bad prose pairs) in tests. Resolved when Joel reads a re-voiced live edition and signs off on the register.
